#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:4
msgid "ulimit - set or get resource usage limits"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:7
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:9
msgid "ulimit [OPTIONS] [LIMIT]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:15
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:17
msgid ""
"``ulimit`` sets or outputs the resource usage limits of the shell and any "
"processes spawned by it. If a new limit value is omitted, the current value "
"of the limit of the resource is printed; otherwise, the specified limit is "
"set to the new value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:19
msgid ""
"Use one of the following switches to specify which resource limit to set or "
"report:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:21
msgid "**-b** or **--socket-buffers**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:22
msgid "The maximum size of socket buffers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:24
msgid "**-c** or **--core-size**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:25
msgid ""
"The maximum size of core files created. By setting this limit to zero, core "
"dumps can be disabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:27
msgid "**-d** or **--data-size**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:28
msgid "The maximum size of a process' data segment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:30
msgid "**-e** or **--nice**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:31
msgid ""
"Controls the maximum nice value; on Linux, this value is subtracted from 20 "
"to give the effective value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:33
msgid "**-f** or **--file-size**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:34
msgid "The maximum size of files created by a process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:36
msgid "**-i** or **--pending-signals**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:37
msgid "The maximum number of signals that may be queued."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:39
msgid "**-l** or **--lock-size**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:40
msgid "The maximum size that may be locked into memory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:42
msgid "**-m** or **--resident-set-size**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:43
msgid "The maximum resident set size."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:45
msgid "**-n** or **--file-descriptor-count**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:46
msgid "The maximum number of open file descriptors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:48
msgid "**-q** or **--queue-size**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:49
msgid "The maximum size of data in POSIX message queues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:51
msgid "**-r** or **--realtime-priority**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:52
msgid "The maximum realtime scheduling priority."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:54
msgid "**-s** or **--stack-size**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:55
msgid "The maximum stack size."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:57
msgid "**-t** or **--cpu-time**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:58
msgid "The maximum amount of CPU time in seconds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:60
msgid "**-u** or **--process-count**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:61
msgid "The maximum number of processes available to the current user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:63
msgid "**-w** or **--swap-size**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:64
msgid "The maximum swap space available to the current user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:66
msgid "**-v** or **--virtual-memory-size**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:67
msgid "The maximum amount of virtual memory available to the shell."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:69
msgid "**-y** or **--realtime-maxtime**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:70
msgid "The maximum contiguous realtime CPU time in microseconds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:72
msgid "**-K** or **--kernel-queues**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:73
msgid "The maximum number of kqueues (kernel queues) for the current user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:75
msgid "**-P** or **--ptys**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:76
msgid "The maximum number of pseudo-terminals for the current user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:78
msgid "**-T** or **--threads**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:79
msgid "The maximum number of simultaneous threads for the current user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:81
msgid ""
"Note that not all these limits are available in all operating systems; "
"consult the documentation for ``setrlimit`` in your operating system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:83
msgid ""
"The value of limit can be a number in the unit specified for the resource or "
"one of the special values ``hard``, ``soft``, or ``unlimited``, which stand "
"for the current hard limit, the current soft limit, and no limit, "
"respectively."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:85
msgid ""
"If limit is given, it is the new value of the specified resource. If no "
"option is given, then **-f** is assumed. Values are in kilobytes, except for "
"**-t**, which is in seconds and **-n** and **-u**, which are unscaled "
"values. The exit status is 0 unless an invalid option or argument is "
"supplied, or an error occurs while setting a new limit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:87
msgid ""
"``ulimit`` also accepts the following options that determine what type of "
"limit to set:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:89
msgid "**-H** or **--hard**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:90
msgid "Sets hard resource limit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:92
msgid "**-S** or **--soft**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:93
msgid "Sets soft resource limit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:95
msgid ""
"A hard limit can only be decreased. Once it is set it cannot be increased; a "
"soft limit may be increased up to the value of the hard limit. If neither **-"
"H** nor **-S** is specified, both the soft and hard limits are updated when "
"assigning a new limit value, and the soft limit is used when reporting the "
"current value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:97
msgid "The following additional options are also understood by ``ulimit``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:99
msgid "**-a** or **--all**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:100
msgid "Prints all current limits."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:102
msgid "**-h** or **--help**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:103
msgid "Displays help about using this command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:105
msgid ""
"The ``fish`` implementation of ``ulimit`` should behave identically to the "
"implementation in bash, except for these differences:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:107
msgid "Fish ``ulimit`` supports GNU-style long options for all switches."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:109
msgid ""
"Fish ``ulimit`` does not support the **-p** option for getting the pipe "
"size. The bash implementation consists of a compile-time check that "
"empirically guesses this number by writing to a pipe and waiting for "
"SIGPIPE. Fish does not do this because this method of determining pipe size "
"is unreliable. Depending on bash version, there may also be further "
"additional limits to set in bash that do not exist in fish."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:111
msgid ""
"Fish ``ulimit`` does not support getting or setting multiple limits in one "
"command, except reporting all values using the **-a** switch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:115
msgid "Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/ulimit.rst:117
msgid "``ulimit -Hs 64`` sets the hard stack size limit to 64 kB."
msgstr ""
